"title": "8726: doubters",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8726: doubters",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture provides examples of believers who express temporary doubts--in particular about the willingness and power of God to deliver his people, the nature of his purpose, and their own place within the divine plan.</p>\n<h2>Examples of those doubting their effectiveness to serve God</h2>\n<h3>Moses</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:11\">EXO 3:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:1\">EXO 4:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:10-Exod4:13\">EXO 4:10–4:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:12\">EXO 6:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:30\">EXO 6:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:13-Num11:15\">NUM 11:13–11:15</a></p>\n<h3>Gideon</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:15\">JDG 6:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:17\">JDG 6:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:36-Judg6:40\">JDG 6:36–6:40</a></p>\n<h3>Elijah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:3-1Kgs19:4\">1KI 19:3–19:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:10\">1KI 19:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:14\">1KI 19:14</a></p>\n<h3>Jeremiah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:6\">JER 1:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer15:10\">JER 15:10</a></p>\n<h2>Those temporarily doubting God's promises</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:8\">GEN 15:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:17-Gen17:18\">GEN 17:17–17:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:12-Gen18:15\">GEN 18:12–18:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:18\">LUK 1:18</a></p>\n<h2>Those doubting God's power</h2>\n<h3>Abraham and Isaac doubt God's protection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:12-Gen12:13\">GEN 12:12–12:13</a></strong> <em>Fearing for his safety, Abraham resorts to deception.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:2\">GEN 20:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:7\">GEN 26:7</a></p>\n<h3>Moses and Israel in the desert</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod5:22-Exod5:23\">EXO 5:22–5:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:10-Exod14:11\">EXO 14:10–14:11</a> <em>The Israelites doubt God's protection at the Red Sea</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:21-Num11:22\">NUM 11:21–11:22</a> <em>Moses doubts God's provision of food</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:31-Num13:33\">NUM 13:31–13:33</a> <em>The ten spies doubt God's power to give victory in Canaan</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:7-Num20:12\">NUM 20:7–20:12</a> <em>Moses strikes the rock twice.</em></p>\n<h3>Others doubting God's deliverance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:11\">1SA 17:11</a> <em>The people of Israel are dismayed by the challenge from Goliath</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:2\">ISA 7:2</a> <em>King Ahaz, afraid of the coalition of Syria and Israel turns to Assyria for help</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:29-Matt14:31\">MAT 14:29–14:31</a> <em>Peter, walking on water, is afraid and begins to sink</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:14-Acts12:15\">ACT 12:14–12:15</a> <em>The early church does not believe that God has released Peter from prison.</em></p>\n<h2>Believers questioning God</h2>\n<h3>Questioning God's actions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:13\">JDG 6:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:10-Num11:12\">NUM 11:10–11:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:3\">NUM 14:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:7-Josh7:8\">JOS 7:7–7:8</a></p>\n<h3>Questioning God's commands</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:2\">1SA 16:2</a> <em>Samuel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:42-2Kgs4:43\">2KI 4:42–4:43</a> <em>Elisha's servant</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:12\">ISA 7:12</a> <em>Ahaz</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:37\">MRK 6:37</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:16-Matt14:17\">MAT 14:16–14:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:13\">LUK 9:13</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:39\">JHN 11:39</a> <em>Martha</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:13-Acts9:14\">ACT 9:13–9:14</a> <em>Ananias</em></p>\n<h2>Believers with doubts about Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:2-Matt11:3\">MAT 11:2–11:3</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:18-Luke7:19\">LUK 7:18–7:19</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:25\">JHN 20:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:17\">MAT 28:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:11-Mark16:14\">MRK 16:11–16:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:25\">LUK 24:25</a></p>",
